review_blob: First Brooklyn experince and really enjoyed it. Nice flavour profile and easily drinkable. Well done.
Absolutely delicious IPA. Beautiful flavours and great aromas. Probably one if BCs best.
Really nice stuff. Smooth with a ton of flavour. Has become one of my favourite American breweries.
Delicious stuff. Really enjoyed it after several IPAs. Would buy again in a heartbeat.
beer_name: Lagunitas A Little Sumpin Sumpin Ale

review_blob: Hoppy maltiness on the nose. Orange golden pour with nice head. Enjoyable mouthfeel and a decent brew.
Beautiful red brown hue. Thick, foamy head but very thin level. Hazelnut and toffee notes on the nose and palate. Smooth and enjoyable. Watch out for 8% as it is well hidden. Drank from 650ml bottle.
Really enjoyable double brown. Malty and delicious. Smooth and easy to drink. Will definitely buy again
Good dark wheat beer. Smooth and enjoyable. Was 5th beer of night so do not remember much else.
Delicious stuff. Caramel hints on the palate. Very smooth and goes down easy. Terrific.
Good stuff. Well balanced and very smooth. Just getting into stouts and find this a pretty good example. On tap from The Archer in Fairhaven, WA
Enjoyable IPA from Seattle. Not too hoppy but with some grapefruit on the nose. Tasty stuff.
Very floral on the nose. Hoppy but goes down very smoothly on the palate. Enjoyable and easy to drink

Beautiful dark copper colour. Nice nose of chocolaty cocoa with groud coffee beans. I might not be accurately describing but that is what comes to  mind. As with other deScriptions i feel it a bit watery on the palate. Decent but not worth chasing.
beer_name: Vancouver Island Sea Dog Amber Ale

review_blob: Absolutely delicious stuff. Gorgeous aromas on the nose. Smooth and easy too drink. Always have some on hand.
Very nice chocolate stout. Smooth and (too) easy to drink. Small foamy head upon pour. Notes of chocolate on nose and palate. Simple but delicious.
Hoppy nose with hints of grapefruit and faint caramel. Golden amber in colour with one inch foamy head. Nice mouthfeel with hints of orange peel. Very good
beer_name: Fernie Lone Wolf India Pale Ale

review_blob: Thisis a fabulous beer. Delicious and beautifully balanced. 10.5% and you can t tell. Candian beer making at its best. Wonderful.
Deep copper colour with off white foamy head. Caramel and nutty notes. The 8% is nicely hidden but the finish has a little bitter metallic finish that could be improved upon. Overall a nice beer
Golden orange colour. Beautiful citrus and caramel notes on the nose. Smooth and well balanced. Really tasty and worth every cent.
Very nice. Golden amber with nice white foamy head. Hints of orange peel on the nose. Smooth and balanced. Well done.
Beautiful white foamy head. Gorgeous banana aromas on the nose. Incredibly smooth and very easy to drink. Really enjoyable.
Very wet vegetable and metallic nose and palate. Very basic and has no outstanding qualities
Nice white head on golden copper body. Not much on the nose other than a slight caramel hit. Caramel malty notes on the palate. Very smooth with nice finish. A very nice lager.
Just so bland. Needs lime wedge for sure to even make this remotely interesting. I guess this would be nice on the beach but there are so many better beers from mexico than this.
Definite citrus notes on the nose with hints of peach and lemon. Very nice light golden colour with foamy head. Smooth with citrusy hints on the palate. Very nice on a hot summer day.

Beautiful roasted coffee and choclate notes. Dark brown in the glass with a nice foam head. Excellent mouthfeel and very smooth. Toasty notes with chocolate and coffee on the palate. This is a delicious porter. Well done. Tasted from a 650ml bottle.
Fairly bland in both nose and palate. Has some caramel and malty flavours but not much else.
Golden copper in the glass. Caramel malty notes on the nose. Smooth on the palate with caramel notes as well. Enjoyable.
Nose is doughy. Doesnt give much else. Golden appearance in the glass with 1/2 inch of foam head after the pour from bottle. Simple lager with hints of honey on the palate. Simple.
